<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1884&amp;p=9550#p9550"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Aero Glass for Windows 8.1 RC2]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1884&amp;p=9550#p9550"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I have no interest in fine-tuning the taskbar transparency, particularly with regard to some other third-party software. From your post it is evident that Aero Glass keeps changing (used to support the taskbar, now doesn't), which makes it particularly difficult to be compatible with it.<br /><br />What I can promise is this:<br />1) If you check the &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; setting, the taskbar will be opaque on a stock unmodified Windows 7, 8 or 8.1<br />2) If you uncheck the &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; setting, Classic Shell will not touch the taskbar, which will allow any other software to have its way with it<br />3) If you check the &quot;Enable Aero Glass&quot; setting, the start menu will be drawn as it is on Windows 7, allowing any software that tries to emulate Windows 7 aero effect to do its work<br /><br />The fact that a combination of &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; and Aero Glass gives you somewhat desirable effect is purely coincidental. Neither me or the Aero Glass developers can guarantee that this will continue to function in the future.<br /></div><br /><br /><br />It sounds great, thank you <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1787">RIPAciD</a> — Mon Dec 16, 2013 1:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Ivo]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-12-15T11:17:48-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-12-15T11:17:48-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1884&amp;p=9534#p9534</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1884&amp;p=9534#p9534"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Aero Glass for Windows 8.1 RC2]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1884&amp;p=9534#p9534"><![CDATA[
I have no interest in fine-tuning the taskbar transparency, particularly with regard to some other third-party software. From your post it is evident that Aero Glass keeps changing (used to support the taskbar, now doesn't), which makes it particularly difficult to be compatible with it.<br /><br />What I can promise is this:<br />1) If you check the &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; setting, the taskbar will be opaque on a stock unmodified Windows 7, 8 or 8.1<br />2) If you uncheck the &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; setting, Classic Shell will not touch the taskbar, which will allow any other software to have its way with it<br />3) If you check the &quot;Enable Aero Glass&quot; setting, the start menu will be drawn as it is on Windows 7, allowing any software that tries to emulate Windows 7 aero effect to do its work<br /><br />The fact that a combination of &quot;Disable taskbar transparency&quot; and Aero Glass gives you somewhat desirable effect is purely coincidental. Neither me or the Aero Glass developers can guarantee that this will continue to function in the future.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sun Dec 15, 2013 11:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
